                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/192: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-26T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 26, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>703. For the personal attention of the Ambassador. Your 1014, September 23, 8
                        p.m.<note n="55" xml:id="d367fn1">Not printed.</note> Campodonico,<note
                        n="56" xml:id="d367fn2">Carlos T. Campodonico, also Chief of the Argentine
                        Purchasing Commission.</note> the New York representative of YPF, informed
                    the Department this afternoon that the Managing Director of YPF, Buenos Aires,
                    had stated categorically over the telephone that the YPF has not sold, is not
                    negotiating the sale of, and will not sell any aviation gasoline to Lati. Please
                    endeavor urgently to ascertain the facts in this matter and telegraph your
                    findings to the Department. Campodonico added that YPF’s entire output of
                    aviation gasoline goes to the Argentine Army and Navy except for some very small
                    quantities to local commercial distributors.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
